Venizelos Says International Environment Affecting Greek Reforms

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-09-16T13:20:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/venizelos-says-international-environment-affecting-greek-reforms.html
Greek Finance Minister Evangelos
Venizelos said the government is determined to meet fiscal
targets for 2011 and 2012 despite an adverse international
environment which affects implementation of reform policies.  “We are decided to meet all our targets,” Venizelos said
in Wroclaw,  Poland , according to an e-mailed transcript of his
comments from the Athens-based ministry today. “To meet our
fiscal target for 2011 and 2012 and reach a primary surplus as
soon as possible to shield our country.”  Venizelos reiterated the Greek banking sector is
“completely secure.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  